{SECT 0 {EXCHG {PARA 18 "" 0 "" {TEXT 280 41 "Dynamic Equations for th
e SEESAW-E System" }}{PARA 257 "" 0 "" {TEXT 256 1 "\251" }{TEXT -1 
29 " 2012 Quanser Consulting Inc." }}{PARA 19 "" 0 "" {TEXT 257 5 "URL
: " }{URLLINK 17 "http://www.quanser.com" 4 "http://www.quanser.com" "
" }}{PARA 256 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 128 "NOTE: This worksheet presents the \+
general dynamic equations modelling a linear track-and-cart system mou
nted on top of a seesaw." }}}{PARA 258 "" 0 "Description" {TEXT -1 0 "
" }}{SECT 0 {PARA 3 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 11 "Description" }}{PARA 15 "" 0 
"" {TEXT -1 114 "This worksheet presents the general dynamic equations
 modelling a seesaw on top of which a linear cart is mounted." }}
{PARA 15 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 90 "Specifically, this worksheet is used to \+
derive the state-space matrices for the Quanser's " }{TEXT 284 6 "Sees
aw" }{TEXT -1 12 " experiment." }}{PARA 15 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 72 "The La
grange's method is used to obtain the dynamic model of the system." }}
{SECT 0 {PARA 4 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "The " }{TEXT 264 13 "Quanser_Tools
" }{TEXT -1 8 " Package" }}{PARA 15 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "The " }{TEXT 
265 13 "Quanser_Tools" }{TEXT -1 228 " module defines generic procedur
es and data in relation to determining the state-space representation \+
of all the Quanser experiments. Specifically, this means deriving and \+
solving the Lagrange's equations of the Quanser systems." }}{PARA 15 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "The " }{TEXT 274 7 "quanser" }{TEXT -1 27 " reposit
ory containing the " }{TEXT 273 13 "Quanser_Tools" }{TEXT -1 50 " pack
age is implemented in the 2 following files: " }{TEXT 275 11 "quanser.
ind" }{TEXT -1 5 " and " }{TEXT 276 12 "quanser.lib." }{TEXT -1 110 " \+
If these two files are not readily available, they can be generated by
 executing the Maple worksheet titled: " }{TEXT 266 17 "quanser_tools.
mws" }{TEXT -1 1 "." }}{PARA 15 "" 0 "" {TEXT 272 10 "To install" }
{TEXT -1 5 " the " }{TEXT 269 13 "Quanser_Tools" }{TEXT -1 29 " packag
e, copy the two files " }{TEXT 267 11 "quanser.ind" }{TEXT -1 5 " and \+
" }{TEXT 268 11 "quanser.lib" }{TEXT -1 98 "  into a directory of your
 choice, like for example: \"C:\\Program Files\\Quanser\\Maple Reposit
ory\". " }}{PARA 15 "" 0 "" {TEXT 271 6 "To use" }{TEXT -1 5 " the " }
{TEXT 270 13 "Quanser_Tools" }{TEXT -1 94 " package in a Maple workshe
et, add the path to its disk location to the Maple global variable " }
{TEXT 277 7 "libname" }{TEXT -1 80 ". For example, this can be achieve
d by the following Maple command: \nlibname := " }{TEXT 278 54 " \"C:/
Program Files/Quanser/Maple Repository\", libname:" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}}{SECT 0 {PARA 3 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 24 "Worksheet Init
ialization" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 41 "restart: inter
face( imaginaryunit = j ): " }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 
22 "with( LinearAlgebra ):" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 
69 "libname := \"C:/Program Files/Quanser/Maple Repository\", \".\", l
ibname:" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 22 "with( Quanser_To
ols );" }}{PARA 12 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#7,%$HTMG%(deriveAG%(deriveBG
%(deriveFG%/kinetic_energyG%3lagrange_equationsG%2moment_of_inertiaG%'
n_normG%1potential_energyG%4write_ABCD_to_MfileG" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 66 "environment variable representing the order of ser
ies calculations" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 11 "Order := 2:" }}
}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}}{SECT 0 {PARA 3 "" 0 "
Notations" {TEXT -1 9 "Notations" }}{SECT 0 {PARA 4 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
25 "Generalized Coordinates: " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "q[i]" "6#&%\"qG6#%\"iG
" }{TEXT -1 2 "'s" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 67 "The generalized coor
dinates are also called Lagrangian coordinates." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{XPPEDIT 18 0 "x[c](t);" "6#-&%\"xG6#%\"cG6#%\"tG" }{TEXT -1 148 " =  \+
driving cart (i.e. IP02 or IP01) linear position: the cart zero positi
on is defined at mid-stroke, at the system's quiescent point of operat
ion." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {XPPEDIT 18 0 "theta(t);" "6#-%&thetaG6#%\"tG
" }{TEXT -1 63 " = Seesaw tilt angle about the horizontal: the zero an
gle [mod " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "2*pi" "6#*&\"\"#\"\"\"%#piGF%" }{TEXT -1 
67 "] is defined when the seesaw is in the perfect horizontal position
." }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 27 "q := [ x[c](t), theta(t
) ];" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%\"qG7$-&%\"xG6#%\"cG6#%\"tG-
%&thetaGF+" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 63 "Nq = number of Lagr
angian coordinates (e.g. here, it is Nq = 2)" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 41 "Nq is also the number of position states." }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 16 "Nq := nops( q ):" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
101 "qd = first-order time derivative of the generalized coordinates, \+
e.g. position and angular velocities" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 
0 24 "qd := map( diff, q, t );" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#q
dG7$-%%diffG6$-&%\"xG6#%\"cG6#%\"tGF/-F'6$-%&thetaGF.F/" }}}}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{SECT 0 {PARA 4 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 56 "Absolute C
artesian Coordinates of the Centre Of Gravity " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 12 "conventions:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 3 "1) " }
{XPPEDIT 18 0 "theta = 0;" "6#/%&thetaG\"\"!" }{TEXT -1 44 " correspon
ds to seesaw perfectly horizontal." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 49 "2) \+
positive rotation is CCW when facing the cart." }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 
"" {TEXT -1 106 "absolute Cartesian coordinates of the Centre Of Gravi
ty (COG) of the seesaw-plus-IP01-or-IP02-track system" }}{PARA 0 "> " 
0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 60 "X[sw] := - D[c] * sin( q[2] );\nY[sw] := D[c] * \+
cos( q[2] );\n" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>&%\"XG6#%#swG,$*&&%
\"DG6#%\"cG\"\"\"-%$sinG6#-%&thetaG6#%\"tGF.!\"\"" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#>&%\"YG6#%#swG*&&%\"DG6#%\"cG\"\"\"-%$cosG6#-%&thetaG6#
%\"tGF-" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 88 "absolute Cartesian coo
rdinates of the IP01 or IP02 linear cart's Centre Of Gravity (COG)" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 44 "remark: the cart slides on top of the see
saw" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 99 "X[c] := - D[T] * sin( q[2] )
 + q[1] * cos( q[2] );\nY[c] := D[T] * cos( q[2] ) + q[1] * sin( q[2] \+
);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>&%\"XG6#%\"cG,&*&&%\"DG6#%\"TG
\"\"\"-%$sinG6#-%&thetaG6#%\"tGF.!\"\"*&-&%\"xGF&F4F.-%$cosGF1F.F." }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>&%\"YG6#%\"cG,&*&&%\"DG6#%\"TG\"\"\"-
%$cosG6#-%&thetaG6#%\"tGF.F.*&-&%\"xGF&F4F.-%$sinGF1F.F." }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 77 "absolute Cartesian velocity coordinates o
f the IP01 or IP02 linear cart's COG" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 
0 51 "Xd[c] := diff( X[c], t );\nYd[c] := diff( Y[c], t );" }}{PARA 
11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>&%#XdG6#%\"cG,(*(&%\"DG6#%\"TG\"\"\"-%$cosG
6#-%&thetaG6#%\"tGF.-%%diffG6$F2F5F.!\"\"*&-F76$-&%\"xGF&F4F5F.F/F.F.*
(F=F.-%$sinGF1F.F6F.F9" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>&%#YdG6#%\"
cG,(*(&%\"DG6#%\"TG\"\"\"-%$sinG6#-%&thetaG6#%\"tGF.-%%diffG6$F2F5F.!
\"\"*&-F76$-&%\"xGF&F4F5F.F/F.F.*(F=F.-%$cosGF1F.F6F.F." }}}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}}{SECT 0 {PARA 4 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 21 "State-Spa
ce Variables" }}{PARA 15 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 103 "The chosen states shoul
d at least include the generalized coordinates and their first-time de
rivatives." }}{PARA 15 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 22 "X is the state vector." }}
{PARA 15 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 141 "In the state vector X: Lagrangian coord
inates are first, followed by their first-time derivatives, and finall
y any other states, as required." }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
78 "Substitution sets for the states (to obtain time-independent state
 equations)." }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 92 "subs_Xq := \{ seq( \+
q[i] = X[i], i=1..Nq ) \};\nsubs_Xqd := \{ seq( qd[i] = X[i+Nq], i=1..
Nq ) \};" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%(subs_XqG<$/-%&thetaG6#%
\"tG&%\"XG6#\"\"#/-&%\"xG6#%\"cGF)&F,6#\"\"\"" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#>%)subs_XqdG<$/-%%diffG6$-%&thetaG6#%\"tGF-&%\"XG6#\"\"
%/-F(6$-&%\"xG6#%\"cGF,F-&F/6#\"\"$" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 34 "Substitution set for the input(s)." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
38 "set the input to be the motor voltage:" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 27 "#subs_U := \{ V[m] = U[1] \}:" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 46 "set the input to be the cart's driving force: " }
{XPPEDIT 18 0 "F[c]" "6#&%\"FG6#%\"cG" }{TEXT -1 56 " (if not expresse
d as a function of the motor voltage): " }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 
1 0 26 "subs_U := \{ F[c] = U[1] \}:" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 66 "Nu = number of inputs; U = input (row) vector (e.g. U = [ V[m] \+
] )" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 21 "Nu := nops( subs_U ):" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 65 "substitution set for the position \+
states' second time derivatives" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 63 "
subs_Xqdd := \{ seq( diff( q[i], t$2 ) =  Xd[i+Nq], i=1..Nq ) \};" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%*subs_XqddG<$/-%%diffG6$-%&thetaG6#%
\"tG-%\"$G6$F-\"\"#&%#XdG6#\"\"%/-F(6$-&%\"xG6#%\"cGF,F.&F36#\"\"$" }}
}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 87 "second time derivatives of the po
sition states (written as time-independent variables)." }}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 91 "The set of unknowns is obtained from this list to so
lve the Lagrange's equations of motion." }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 
1 0 37 "Xqdd := [ seq( Xd[i+Nq], i=1..Nq ) ];" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#>%%XqddG7$&%#XdG6#\"\"$&F'6#\"\"%" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 70 "substitution set to linearize the state-space matr
ices (i.e. A and B) " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 65 "about the quiesce
nt null state vector (small-displacement theory)" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 72 "subs_XUzero := \{ seq( X[i] = 0, i=1..2*Nq ), seq( U[
i] = 0, i=1..Nu ) \}:" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 83 "Nx = dim
( X ) = total number of states (should be greater than or equal to: 2 \+
* Nq)" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 29 "Ny = chosen number of outputs" }
}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 27 "Nx := 2 * Nq + 0:\nNy := N
q:" }}}}}{SECT 0 {PARA 3 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 50 "Total Potential and Kine
tic Energies of the System" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 94 "The total p
otential and kinetic energies are needed to calculate the Lagrangian o
f the system." }}{SECT 0 {PARA 4 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 24 "Total Potential \+
Energy: " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "V[T];" "6#&%\"VG6#%\"TG" }{TEXT -1 1 " " }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 90 "The total potential energy can be express
ed in terms of the generalized coordinates alone." }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 52 "Ve[T] = Total Elastic Potential Energy of the syst
em" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 12 "Ve[T] := 0: " }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 50 "IP01 or IP02 cart's gravitational potenti
al energy" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 54 "Vg[c] := potential_ene
rgy( 'gravity', m[c], g, Y[c] );" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>&
%#VgG6#%\"cG*(&%\"mGF&\"\"\"%\"gGF+,&*&&%\"DG6#%\"TGF+-%$cosG6#-%&thet
aG6#%\"tGF+F+*&-&%\"xGF&F8F+-%$sinGF5F+F+F+" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 83 "gravitational potential energy of the one-seesaw-plus-o
ne-IP01-or-IP02-track system" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 57 "Vg[
sw] := potential_energy( 'gravity', m[sw], g, Y[sw] );" }}{PARA 11 "" 
1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>&%#VgG6#%#swG**&%\"mGF&\"\"\"%\"gGF+&%\"DG6#%\"cG
F+-%$cosG6#-%&thetaG6#%\"tGF+" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 58 "
Vg[T] = Total Gravitational Potential Energy of the system" }}{PARA 0 
"> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 24 "Vg[T] := Vg[c] + Vg[sw]:" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 43 "V[T] = Total Potential Energy of the system" }}
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 34 "V[T] := simplify( Ve[T] + Vg[T] );
" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>&%\"VG6#%\"TG*&%\"gG\"\"\",(*(&%
\"mG6#%\"cGF*&%\"DGF&F*-%$cosG6#-%&thetaG6#%\"tGF*F**(F-F*-&%\"xGF/F8F
*-%$sinGF5F*F**(&F.6#%#swGF*&F2F/F*F3F*F*F*" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 0 "" }}}{SECT 0 {PARA 4 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 22 "Total Kinetic Energy: \+
" }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "T[T];" "6#&%\"TG6#F$" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
115 "The total kinetic energy can be expressed in terms of the general
ized coordinates and their first-time derivatives." }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 65 "The cart's directions of translation and rotation \+
are orthogonal." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {XPPEDIT 18 0 "Tr[c];" "6#&%#TrG6#%
\"cG" }{TEXT -1 60 " = kinetic energy due to rotation tied to the moto
rized cart" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {XPPEDIT 18 0 "J[m]" "6#&%\"JG6#%\"mG" }
{TEXT -1 27 " = motor armature inertia; " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "K[g]" "6#&%
\"KG6#%\"gG" }{TEXT -1 15 " = gear ratio; " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "r[mp]" "6#
&%\"rG6#%#mpG" }{TEXT -1 22 " = motor pinion radius" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 
"" {MPLTEXT 1 0 58 "Tr[c] := kinetic_energy( 'rotation', J[m], omega[m
](t) ): " }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 36 "omega[m](t) := K[g] * q
d[1] / r[mp]:" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 16 "'Tr[c]' = Tr[c];" 
}}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#/&%#TrG6#%\"cG,$*&#\"\"\"\"\"#F+**&%
\"JG6#%\"mGF+&%\"KG6#%\"gGF,-%%diffG6$-&%\"xGF&6#%\"tGF=F,&%\"rG6#%#mp
G!\"#F+F+" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 34 "from the IP02 or IP0
1 parameters: " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "J[m]*K[g]^2/(r[mp]^2);" "6#*(&%\"JG6#%
\"mG\"\"\"*$&%\"KG6#%\"gG\"\"#F(*$&%\"rG6#%#mpGF.!\"\"" }{TEXT -1 13 "
 < 0.14 kg < " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "Mm[c];" "6#&%#MmG6#%\"cG" }}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 53 "The cart's rotational kinetic energy can be neglecte
d" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 11 "Tr[c] := 0:" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }{TEXT -1 6 "or if:" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 32 "M[rc] = J[m] * K[g]^2 / r[mp]^2:" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }{TEXT -1 4 "then" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 
1 0 30 "Tr[c] = 1/2 * m[rc] * qd[1]^2:" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 153 "V[c] = IP01 or IP02 Cartesian linear velocity \nEuclidia
n norm (i.e. magnitude) of the absolute Cartesian (linear) velocity of
 the IP01 or IP02 cart's COG" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 69 "V[c
] := n_norm( [ Xd[c], Yd[c] ], 2 ):\nV[c] := combine( V[c], trig );" }
}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>&%\"VG6#%\"cG*$,**&)&%\"DG6#%\"TG\"
\"#\"\"\")-%%diffG6$-%&thetaG6#%\"tGF9F0F1F1**F0F1F,F1F3F1-F46$-&%\"xG
F&F8F9F1!\"\"*$)F;F0F1F1*&)F=F0F1F2F1F1#F1F0" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {XPPEDIT 18 0 "Tt[c]" "6#&%#TtG6#%\"cG" }{TEXT -1 73 " = translation
al kinetic energy of the motorized cart (e.g. IP02 or IP01)" }}{PARA 
